WEBVTT

00:34.659 --> 00:36.578
Previously on "Twenties"...

00:36.619 --> 00:38.371
I ain't never cared
            about a woman

00:38.413 --> 00:39.622
the way I care about you.

00:39.664 --> 00:41.833
I don't want nobody to know
     about what we got going on.

00:41.875 --> 00:42.625
This is for us.

00:42.667 --> 00:44.461
I been taking a lot
         of these meetings.

00:44.502 --> 00:46.379
This is the first one
            I actually like.

00:46.421 --> 00:47.380
The Ballet Russe program.

00:47.422 --> 00:48.715
I can't believe
            you did this.

00:48.757 --> 00:50.341
I hope that you have
         a wonderful birthday.

00:51.760 --> 00:54.137
What a nice surprise.

00:54.179 --> 00:55.513
We don't know
        each other like that?

00:55.555 --> 00:57.265
-We don't.
            -Bye, Hattie.

00:57.307 --> 00:58.349
This isn't working for me.

00:58.391 --> 01:00.477
-I think of you often.
           -Is that right?

01:00.518 --> 01:02.062
-That's mine?
            -Last straw?

01:02.103 --> 01:03.063
Oh, yeah.

01:03.104 --> 01:04.064
Marie tripping again.

01:04.105 --> 01:05.398
Can I stay with you?

01:11.863 --> 01:14.199
Vibing in a trance

01:14.240 --> 01:16.117
I don't understand

01:16.159 --> 01:20.580
Oh, oh, oh, oh

01:20.622 --> 01:22.624
Feel it in your hands

01:22.665 --> 01:26.211
There's some kind of magic

01:27.712 --> 01:29.798
Mm, pick 'em up.

01:29.839 --> 01:31.382
I don't like this game.

01:31.424 --> 01:34.385
That's 'cause you losin'
     with your competitive ass.

01:34.427 --> 01:37.263
-It's not a game of skill.
          -Are you serious?

01:37.305 --> 01:40.600
Are there any
    Bruno tournaments out there?

01:40.642 --> 01:43.353
Now that you mention it,
       nah, there ain't none.

01:43.394 --> 01:44.813
I wonder why.

01:44.854 --> 01:46.147
I might have to start one.

01:46.189 --> 01:48.483
You know, me and my cousins
        would pay top dollar

01:48.525 --> 01:50.610
to compete in a triples
       and doubles game, easy.

01:50.652 --> 01:52.278
You're making me
           feel old again.

01:52.320 --> 01:53.446
Well, you look young,

01:53.488 --> 01:55.031
so that's all that matters,
               right?

01:55.073 --> 01:56.616
Mm, that's sweet.

01:56.658 --> 01:57.617
Oh, yeah.

01:57.659 --> 02:00.245
Babe, you didn't say Bruno.
         Pick up four cards.

02:00.286 --> 02:01.454
You just called me babe.

02:01.496 --> 02:03.414
light music

02:03.456 --> 02:05.041
Did you hear that?

02:05.083 --> 02:07.752
-Now you're losing.
            -Ahh...am I?

02:07.794 --> 02:13.049
Places that we've
              never gone

02:15.426 --> 02:17.178
I wanna feel crafty

02:17.220 --> 02:19.889
Babe, we gotta get
        a Black marching band

02:19.931 --> 02:21.015
for our reception.

02:21.057 --> 02:22.642
My cousin Crystal said
          she knows a guy.

02:22.684 --> 02:25.186
So, what, like
    a wedding-themed "Drumline"?

02:25.228 --> 02:27.522
Well, it's an homage
              to HBCUs.

02:27.564 --> 02:31.359
Well, I love an HBCU,
     but can we maybe just table

02:31.401 --> 02:34.904
the wedding talk for a bit
      and enjoy the engagement?

02:34.946 --> 02:36.156
You're right.

02:36.197 --> 02:38.491
I'm treating the engagement
         like Thanksgiving.

02:38.533 --> 02:40.827
We haven't even marinated
        the turkey legs yet,

02:40.869 --> 02:43.413
and I'm already out here
       buying Christmas gifts.

02:45.874 --> 02:47.876
Um, let me just...

02:50.086 --> 02:51.171
Hello?

02:51.212 --> 02:53.590
So I loved the book.

02:53.631 --> 02:55.425
Took you long enough.

02:57.302 --> 02:59.846
So you do have good taste.

02:59.888 --> 03:02.265
If I didn't like it,

03:02.307 --> 03:04.184
wouldn't mean
       I don't got good taste.

03:04.225 --> 03:06.352
Just mean we like
           different things.

03:06.394 --> 03:08.271
I guess that's fair.

03:08.521 --> 03:11.566
So let's make
              this movie.

03:11.608 --> 03:14.903
Well, I mean,
   let's lock in the rights first.

03:14.944 --> 03:18.865
Whatever we gotta do,
   I'm ready to lock in with you.

03:21.618 --> 03:26.039
Me too. I'm locked in too.

03:26.080 --> 03:27.207
Enjoy your day.

03:29.083 --> 03:32.045
upbeat music

03:35.673 --> 03:38.218
Where have you been?
     I haven't seen you in days.

03:38.259 --> 03:39.552
I been at my boo's house.

03:39.594 --> 03:41.512
Ida's not your boo.

03:41.554 --> 03:43.264
Then why did I just spend
         the last two hours

03:43.306 --> 03:44.390
soaking in her tub?

03:44.432 --> 03:45.725
Because you like
      playing house with people

03:45.767 --> 03:48.519
that have no intention
        of committing to you.

03:48.561 --> 03:50.438
I was just trying
       to give you your space.

03:50.480 --> 03:52.732
No, you like
         being up under Ida.

03:52.774 --> 03:55.693
That's true.
   But I also been writing though.

03:55.735 --> 03:59.113
Good for you.
    What are you doing for money?

03:59.155 --> 04:01.908
Ida B's been
      helping me out, you know.

04:01.950 --> 04:04.369
Oh, so you kept now?

04:04.410 --> 04:06.496
No.

04:06.537 --> 04:08.456
I got a little money saved up.

04:08.498 --> 04:11.167
Not enough
       to pay you rent though.

04:11.209 --> 04:13.169
Uh-huh.

04:18.132 --> 04:20.385
Can't let you get away

04:27.809 --> 04:29.560
Your scenes don't rehearse
         until after lunch.

04:29.602 --> 04:32.188
I know. I just wanted
        to get a head start.

04:32.230 --> 04:33.481
I'm serious about my craft.

04:33.523 --> 04:34.774
I wish you were as serious

04:34.816 --> 04:36.484
about your
       social media presence.

04:36.526 --> 04:37.527
Excuse me?

04:37.568 --> 04:39.153
We tried to get
       your account verified,

04:39.195 --> 04:40.989
but your followers
            were too low.

04:41.030 --> 04:41.781
I know.

04:41.823 --> 04:43.283
I--I rarely post,
           and when I do,

04:43.324 --> 04:45.660
I'm trying to get people
      to come to my yoga class.

04:45.702 --> 04:48.037
I just--I don't get it.

04:48.079 --> 04:49.289
I never have.

04:49.330 --> 04:51.416
I want to be one
         with the universe,

04:51.457 --> 04:52.792
not with the internet.

04:52.834 --> 04:54.544
Some of the most famous actors
            in the world

04:54.585 --> 04:55.670
don't even have social media.

04:55.712 --> 04:58.047
-You're not famous.
               -Right.

04:58.089 --> 05:00.133
But I don't wanna be famous.

05:00.174 --> 05:01.217
I wanna be a good actor.

05:01.259 --> 05:03.177
Most good actors are famous.

05:03.219 --> 05:05.596
Right, again.

05:05.638 --> 05:09.475
Your platform should reflect
       the life that you want,

05:09.517 --> 05:11.978
not the life you have.

05:12.020 --> 05:14.939
punchy music

05:19.944 --> 05:21.571
Hattie!

05:21.612 --> 05:24.490
Oh, my God,
      it's so good to see you.

05:24.532 --> 05:25.533
Hey.

05:25.575 --> 05:28.036
What's up, Courtney?
            You miss me?

05:28.077 --> 05:30.496
I miss you doing all the
    busy work around the office.

05:30.538 --> 05:33.124
Mm, yeah.
         It sucks, don't it?

05:33.166 --> 05:34.375
-Yeah.
               -Okay.

05:34.417 --> 05:36.961
I still can't believe
     Ida B. fired you like that.

05:37.003 --> 05:39.297
At least you look like you're
     still keeping it together.

05:39.339 --> 05:42.633
Oh, yeah, trust me.
      All is well in my world.

05:42.675 --> 05:43.718
Why so chipper?

05:43.760 --> 05:45.386
Well, I can't really
            get into it,

05:45.428 --> 05:46.804
but just know, you know,

05:46.846 --> 05:49.015
things are really looking up
           for your girl.

05:49.057 --> 05:50.141
Oh.

05:52.310 --> 05:54.187
What up, fam?

05:55.646 --> 05:58.399
I, um, will take the usual.

05:58.441 --> 06:00.443
Americano
       and a raspberry scone?

06:00.485 --> 06:02.862
Damn, you know me so well.

06:06.115 --> 06:07.617
Thank you.

06:08.868 --> 06:10.286
Sorry, your card
            was declined.

06:10.328 --> 06:12.205
What? You--

06:12.246 --> 06:13.373
Run it--run it again.

06:13.414 --> 06:15.249
Card was declined.

06:15.291 --> 06:17.460
Yo, I know I got money.

06:17.502 --> 06:18.586
I believe you.

06:18.628 --> 06:19.921
Just let me take
       the next person in line

06:19.962 --> 06:22.465
while you figure out
          what's going on.

06:28.638 --> 06:31.724
Ugh, oh, my God.
       I hope it isn't fraud.

06:31.766 --> 06:34.185
You know, my last bank
       was terrible with that,

06:34.227 --> 06:35.645
but I didn't complain,

06:35.686 --> 06:37.563
because I made a commitment
        to go an entire year

06:37.605 --> 06:39.941
without asking for the manager.

06:39.982 --> 06:42.568
Fighting off
       those toxic instincts.

06:42.610 --> 06:44.445
Damn it.

06:44.487 --> 06:47.281
Yo, I forgot to turn off
             my autopay.

06:47.323 --> 06:48.741
My student loans
       went through yesterday

06:48.783 --> 06:50.243
and took all my money.

06:50.284 --> 06:52.620
I'll pay for your coffee.

06:52.662 --> 06:54.539
Thank you, Courtney.

06:54.580 --> 06:57.041
Ah, look
       at Black women uniting.

06:57.083 --> 06:58.668
You know, I would have paid
          for your coffee,

06:58.709 --> 07:00.461
but I didn't wanna flaunt
            my privilege.

07:00.503 --> 07:02.630
Well, you can still
            buy my scone.

07:02.672 --> 07:04.298
I don't wanna
         be a white savior.

07:05.508 --> 07:06.551
Yes, Ida.

07:06.592 --> 07:08.010
Are you making
               the beans?

07:08.052 --> 07:10.346
I'm on my way.

07:16.185 --> 07:18.729
What do people want?

07:18.771 --> 07:23.151
They want good,
        clean entertainment.

07:23.192 --> 07:24.694
They don't want trauma.

07:24.735 --> 07:25.945
They get that from the news.

07:25.987 --> 07:27.363
When it comes
          to entertainment,

07:27.405 --> 07:29.157
people wanna be happy,
           they want joy,

07:29.198 --> 07:31.492
they wanna feel like
     they're getting a warm hug.

07:31.534 --> 07:32.994
If that's what they want,
          then they should

07:33.035 --> 07:35.037
get a massage,
        not go to the movies.

07:35.079 --> 07:36.581
When people
    go to the movies, they wanna

07:36.622 --> 07:38.833
forget their problems,
      not be reminded of them.

07:38.875 --> 07:40.877
So what do you propose?

07:40.918 --> 07:42.712
We start making movies
     that have happy characters

07:42.753 --> 07:44.839
that have happy lives
   that always get happy endings.

07:44.881 --> 07:47.341
What about all the movies
    that we all loved growing up?

07:47.383 --> 07:49.802
Mm, get with the times, okay?

07:49.844 --> 07:52.054
People have enough trauma
      in their lives right now.

07:52.096 --> 07:53.514
"Boyz n the Hood"--
         people thought that

07:53.556 --> 07:56.017
"Boyz n the Hood"
         would incite riots.

07:56.058 --> 07:57.518
It didn't.

07:57.560 --> 07:59.228
It actually promoted
             nonviolence

07:59.270 --> 08:00.521
because it showed audiences

08:00.563 --> 08:02.690
how devastating
       gun violence could be.

08:02.732 --> 08:06.402
Art isn't supposed to be nice.

08:06.444 --> 08:10.031
It's supposed
        to show us ourselves.

08:10.573 --> 08:13.451
I don't care if our movies
       are traumatic or nice.

08:13.493 --> 08:16.621
-I want them to make money.
            -You the man.

08:16.662 --> 08:18.498
Okay. Thanks, everybody.

08:24.795 --> 08:27.089
Congratulations.

08:27.131 --> 08:30.635
Oh...ha. Thanks.

08:30.676 --> 08:32.803
Chuck's a lucky guy.

08:39.477 --> 08:40.811
I have a lunch.

08:40.853 --> 08:43.940
-Me too, yeah.
      -Well, talk to you later.

08:43.981 --> 08:46.526
-Yeah, later.
               -Later.

08:55.493 --> 08:56.953
-You know her?
               -I do.

08:56.994 --> 08:59.372
She's actually coming tonight.

08:59.413 --> 09:01.624
-Tonight?
      -Yeah. She's cute, right?

09:01.666 --> 09:04.627
Okay...
            She is cute.

09:04.669 --> 09:06.546
Me like her...

09:08.714 --> 09:10.633
-Hmm, hm.
                -Mm.

09:10.675 --> 09:12.718
Should I start
      one of those social media

09:12.760 --> 09:14.053
subscription accounts?

09:14.095 --> 09:16.472
Why, you trying to sell
       pictures of your toes?

09:16.514 --> 09:19.225
No, but they seem
         to be very popular.

09:20.768 --> 09:23.062
Do you even know
        what a SoleyStans is?

09:23.104 --> 09:24.188
No.

09:24.230 --> 09:26.899
You don't know how
     social media works, do you?

09:27.692 --> 09:30.486
I don't. How do you do it?

09:30.528 --> 09:32.738
I mean, you know,
       for me it's different.

09:32.780 --> 09:35.032
I mean, I'm trying to be
   a comedy writer, so I'm mostly

09:35.074 --> 09:37.451
just post a bunch of silly
     memes and stuff like that.

09:37.493 --> 09:39.328
But you don't even write
            those memes.

09:39.370 --> 09:41.038
-You just post them.
              -Exactly.

09:41.080 --> 09:44.417
But I only share the ones
   that I think are really funny.

09:44.458 --> 09:46.168
-That doesn't make any sense.
              -I mean,

09:46.210 --> 09:49.297
do you at least comment
     on other people's pictures?

09:49.338 --> 09:51.632
No, because I'm an empath

09:51.674 --> 09:52.883
and I can tell people
            are on there

09:52.925 --> 09:55.469
acting like they're happy
      when they're really not.

09:55.511 --> 09:58.639
-That's the whole point.
            -To be fake?

09:58.681 --> 09:59.849
Yes.

09:59.890 --> 10:03.185
Nobody wants to tell the truth
          on social media.

10:03.603 --> 10:05.646
No wonder I'm not
             good at it.

10:05.688 --> 10:07.273
Look, when you're acting,

10:07.315 --> 10:09.942
don't you have to step
     into somebody else's truth?

10:09.984 --> 10:11.068
-Yeah.
               -Okay.

10:11.110 --> 10:13.654
Then step into whatever truth
          you wanna be in.

10:13.696 --> 10:16.699
If you wanna be fabulous,
       pretend to be fabulous.

10:16.741 --> 10:19.619
If you wanna be rich,
    post pictures of rich people.

10:19.660 --> 10:22.163
I'm telling you,
     you can manifest that shit.

10:22.204 --> 10:24.040
I don't think
        that's how it works.

10:24.081 --> 10:25.499
Well, you know,
      you gotta treat that shit

10:25.541 --> 10:27.418
like it's a full-time job.

10:27.460 --> 10:28.419
So I have to teach yoga,

10:28.461 --> 10:29.837
do my acting gig,
          and pretend like

10:29.879 --> 10:32.173
I live a fabulous life
          on social media?

10:32.214 --> 10:33.591
Mm-hmm.

10:33.633 --> 10:37.178
Damn, that does sound
         like a lot of work.

10:37.219 --> 10:40.556
-Yeah.
     -I'm glad I'm not a actor.

10:46.771 --> 10:49.482
Well, look who's got a phone.

10:49.523 --> 10:51.317
Hello, beautiful humans.

10:51.359 --> 10:54.737
I'm gonna give y'all some time
         to come into the room.

10:54.779 --> 10:57.406
Today we are discussing

10:57.448 --> 11:00.201
meditation and self-love.

11:00.242 --> 11:02.536
I know a lot of y'all
     been asking me to do a live

11:02.578 --> 11:05.081
about this,
      but I need y'all to know

11:05.122 --> 11:06.749
I'm on my own
         self-love journey,

11:06.791 --> 11:10.086
so you gotta have
       some patience with me,

11:10.127 --> 11:11.796
'cause yeah,
        there are still days

11:11.837 --> 11:15.800
where I forget to meditate
    and I don't put myself first.

11:15.841 --> 11:18.344
So we all on a journey
              together.

11:19.887 --> 11:23.140
Striving for perfection
                is what?

11:23.182 --> 11:26.310
That's right, a fool's errand.

11:26.352 --> 11:28.020
True.

11:33.401 --> 11:35.152
Hello! Welcome everyone.

11:35.194 --> 11:37.655
Thank you for gracing me
         with your presence,

11:37.697 --> 11:39.740
and thank you
      for paying me in advance.

11:39.782 --> 11:41.826
It means so much.

11:41.867 --> 11:44.578
Now, I need you all
      to pull out your phones.

11:44.620 --> 11:48.082
soft music

11:48.124 --> 11:50.626
Please do me the honor
           of following me

11:50.668 --> 11:52.253
on all my social media
             platforms.

11:52.294 --> 11:55.631
I need your fellowship
     as well as your followship.

11:59.510 --> 12:02.263
Now let us begin.

12:03.013 --> 12:06.475
Deep breath in...

12:06.517 --> 12:08.519
and exhale.

12:12.273 --> 12:13.399
To us.

12:19.905 --> 12:22.783
I know things have been crazy
        since the engagement.

12:22.825 --> 12:24.952
And I'm sorry
         for bombarding you

12:24.994 --> 12:28.622
with emails about venues,
           cakes, tuxedos.

12:28.664 --> 12:30.666
I know the spreadsheets
             are a lot.

12:30.708 --> 12:32.418
They are.

12:32.460 --> 12:33.961
It's the Capricorn in me.

12:34.003 --> 12:35.588
I know.

12:38.007 --> 12:40.092
Can I ask you something?

12:40.134 --> 12:43.512
-Anything.
           -Why the rush?

12:43.554 --> 12:45.264
What do you mean?

12:45.306 --> 12:46.599
We've been talking
           about marriage

12:46.640 --> 12:47.767
since we started dating.

12:47.808 --> 12:51.645
I know, but something
        about it just feels--

12:51.687 --> 12:54.106
Do you want
        a longer engagement?

12:54.148 --> 12:56.025
That can be arranged.

12:56.066 --> 12:59.403
No, I'm fine.

13:15.586 --> 13:17.963
I have notes.

13:18.005 --> 13:19.006
What?

13:19.048 --> 13:20.841
I read your script again.

13:20.883 --> 13:22.551
You liked it that much, huh?

13:22.593 --> 13:24.178
No, I just wanted
            to make sure

13:24.220 --> 13:27.807
it was as slow and muddled
        as I thought it was.

13:27.848 --> 13:29.058
-What?
               -Yeah.

13:29.099 --> 13:31.143
I like to read scripts twice
        before I give notes.

13:31.185 --> 13:33.813
I like to be very thorough
          with my feedback.

13:35.272 --> 13:37.817
Damn. Did you like any of it?

13:37.858 --> 13:39.235
I liked the opening.

13:39.276 --> 13:42.738
You definitely grabbed
      my attention right away,

13:42.780 --> 13:46.617
but you have to move
         the story forward.

13:46.659 --> 13:47.785
I mean, by the end of it all,

13:47.827 --> 13:49.119
your characters
       were in the same place.

13:49.161 --> 13:51.038
Well, I thought
          in--in episodic,

13:51.080 --> 13:52.957
the characters aren't supposed
        to change that much.

13:52.998 --> 13:54.917
You know, like in television,
          things have to--

13:54.959 --> 13:56.418
The consistency is key. Yes.

13:56.460 --> 14:00.756
But you need to evolve
     your characters over time.

14:00.798 --> 14:01.841
Okay, well, how do I do that

14:01.882 --> 14:03.259
without changing them
              too much?

14:03.300 --> 14:04.260
You have to keep
            putting them

14:04.301 --> 14:06.053
in uncomfortable situations

14:06.095 --> 14:08.180
or have them encounter
          other characters

14:08.222 --> 14:09.598
that are the exact
          opposite of them

14:09.640 --> 14:12.852
so they can see things
    from a different perspective.

14:12.893 --> 14:14.144
So what you saying?

14:14.186 --> 14:15.437
I gotta change
          my whole script?

14:15.479 --> 14:17.940
No, but you can't just
           write a script

14:17.982 --> 14:19.400
and decide you're done.

14:19.441 --> 14:21.610
So when do you know
          that you're done?

14:21.652 --> 14:24.405
It's just a--a feeling.

14:24.446 --> 14:26.073
It took me a long time
          to recognize it,

14:26.115 --> 14:28.576
but I mean,
      now I know when to stop.

14:28.617 --> 14:30.661
Well, when will I know?

14:30.703 --> 14:33.122
You got a few more years.

14:33.163 --> 14:37.167
A--a few more years, really?

14:37.209 --> 14:40.838
Becoming a good writer
         takes time, Hattie.

14:40.880 --> 14:42.464
You finally got a good script.

14:42.506 --> 14:44.133
Great, now it's time
         to make it better.

14:44.174 --> 14:48.220
Look, my--my show is
    for a younger audience, okay?

14:48.262 --> 14:49.889
You just don't get it.

14:49.930 --> 14:51.640
-Don't get defensive.
              -I'm not.

14:51.682 --> 14:53.976
I--I just don't think
    you can give a bunch of notes

14:54.018 --> 14:55.436
for a show
      that's not meant for you.

14:55.477 --> 14:57.813
The execs that you're trying
       to sell this script to

14:57.855 --> 14:59.148
are older than me.

14:59.189 --> 15:01.400
Well, Marie's an exec,
          and she's my age.

15:01.442 --> 15:03.944
She also doesn't have
             much power.

15:03.986 --> 15:05.279
So what you saying?

15:05.321 --> 15:07.656
I gotta write stuff
     that old people will like?

15:07.698 --> 15:09.950
Are you calling me old?

15:09.992 --> 15:12.912
Here we go. Of course not.

15:12.953 --> 15:15.331
I'm just saying you told me
           to be authentic

15:15.372 --> 15:17.499
and to--to write what I know.

15:17.541 --> 15:20.377
But I'm young,
       I'm Black, and I'm gay.

15:20.419 --> 15:24.048
So if the execs are old,
        white, and straight,

15:24.089 --> 15:25.883
how am I supposed to get ahead?

15:25.925 --> 15:27.426
-The same way I did.
                -How?

15:27.468 --> 15:30.471
By being specific
           yet relatable.

15:31.055 --> 15:32.556
That don't even make sense.

15:32.598 --> 15:34.892
My shows are geared
         toward Black women.

15:34.934 --> 15:36.185
-Okay.
      -That's who I write for.

15:36.226 --> 15:38.687
But most of the execs
    who helped get my shows made

15:38.729 --> 15:40.314
are white men.

15:40.356 --> 15:41.357
Now, they don't know
           what it's like

15:41.398 --> 15:43.150
to walk through the world
          as a Black woman,

15:43.192 --> 15:44.944
but they can tell
         by reading my work

15:44.985 --> 15:47.112
that is not just Black women
          who will like it.

15:47.154 --> 15:48.447
So will other people.

15:48.489 --> 15:49.657
And just because
           the protagonist

15:49.698 --> 15:52.368
of "Cocoa's Butter"
    is a Black woman doesn't mean

15:52.409 --> 15:55.204
that you have to be
   a Black woman to relate to her.

15:55.245 --> 15:57.456
So again, it's specific to me,

15:57.498 --> 15:59.249
but other people
         can connect to it.

15:59.291 --> 16:01.669
Well, I don't need everybody
       to connect to my stuff.

16:01.710 --> 16:05.089
Like, as long as I connect
       to it, I'm good, so...

16:05.130 --> 16:07.132
Just what networks want,

16:07.174 --> 16:10.052
a show with an audience of one.

16:10.094 --> 16:13.263
-I was just trying to help you.
      -Did I ask for your help?

16:13.305 --> 16:16.350
No, no, but maybe
          you should have.

16:16.392 --> 16:18.352
You don't know everything.

16:18.394 --> 16:21.188
I know a lot more than you.

16:21.647 --> 16:24.108
You know what?
     I'ma go ahead and head out.

16:24.149 --> 16:26.360
Are you serious?

16:26.944 --> 16:27.861
Yeah, I am.

16:27.903 --> 16:30.072
I'ma--I'ma go work
            on my script.

16:30.114 --> 16:31.991
Hattie, don't be like that.

16:34.284 --> 16:36.203
Be like what?

16:36.245 --> 16:38.956
You told me
      my shit was good, right?

16:38.998 --> 16:42.501
Well, I'ma go make it better.

16:44.878 --> 16:47.923
soft instrumental music

17:08.193 --> 17:11.030
This one's on the house.

17:11.071 --> 17:12.865
Thank you.

17:12.906 --> 17:15.159
You okay?

17:15.200 --> 17:17.870
Yeah.
       You know, life is good.

17:17.911 --> 17:20.456
-It doesn't look like it.
                -Why?

17:20.497 --> 17:22.207
I got some crust in my eye?

17:22.249 --> 17:26.545
No, you just seem
           a little lost.

17:28.088 --> 17:32.426
Yeah.
        You be knowing, man.

17:34.094 --> 17:35.679
What's up?

17:35.721 --> 17:38.140
Well, I was feeling
      pretty good about myself

17:38.182 --> 17:40.142
until I realized
          I keep repeating

17:40.184 --> 17:42.102
the same patterns in my life.

17:42.144 --> 17:44.188
I got rid of
       one toxic relationship

17:44.229 --> 17:46.482
and walked right
          into another one.

17:46.523 --> 17:51.445
I find myself picking my shit
     up off the pavement, again.

17:51.487 --> 17:54.615
I'm still broke as hell,
             as you saw.

17:55.949 --> 17:57.326
Yeah.

17:57.367 --> 18:00.120
And the one thing--
            the one thing

18:00.162 --> 18:02.998
that I was feeling good about,
        which was my script,

18:03.040 --> 18:06.085
she told me it was just okay.

18:06.126 --> 18:08.170
Who?

18:08.212 --> 18:10.422
This woman that I'm seeing.

18:12.466 --> 18:14.301
What'd she say about it?

18:14.343 --> 18:18.388
-That it needed a lot of work.
                -So?

18:18.430 --> 18:20.474
What you mean, so?

18:20.516 --> 18:22.392
That shit hurt my feelings.

18:22.434 --> 18:26.146
Nobody likes getting notes,
     but that's part of the job.

18:26.188 --> 18:28.232
Everything ain't
      gonna come easy, Hattie.

18:28.273 --> 18:30.359
But nothing comes easy
               for me.

18:30.400 --> 18:31.610
I mean, damn,

18:31.652 --> 18:33.112
could something go smooth
        in my life for once--

18:33.153 --> 18:36.198
-You choose chaos.
            -No, I don't.

18:36.240 --> 18:38.534
Look, don't be mad
      'cause you ain't my type.

18:38.575 --> 18:41.245
Tch, girl, please.
        This ain't about me.

18:41.286 --> 18:42.496
This is about you.

18:42.538 --> 18:44.915
So you can keep sitting here
       and nursing this scone,

18:44.957 --> 18:48.961
or you can take your ass home
     and go work on your script.

18:50.712 --> 18:53.382
Yo, why you always
   gotta hit me with the Ted talk?

18:53.423 --> 18:55.384
Because,
      left to your own devices,

18:55.425 --> 18:58.637
you don't get very far.

19:00.639 --> 19:03.058
If you want, you can join
         my writers' group.

19:03.100 --> 19:04.476
We try to meet once a week.

19:04.518 --> 19:07.896
Nah, I don't know.
      I like writing by myself.

19:07.938 --> 19:09.940
How's that working out
              for you?

19:15.237 --> 19:17.531
Yo...

19:17.573 --> 19:20.659
text me the information
       when you get a chance.

19:42.806 --> 19:44.266
You like that?

19:44.308 --> 19:47.019
Yes.

19:47.060 --> 19:47.936
Show me.

19:51.940 --> 19:53.567
More.

19:58.697 --> 20:01.909
-Show more, Marie.
               -Ooh...

20:01.950 --> 20:03.952
I got you.

20:11.710 --> 20:14.171
I got an appointment
         with Estelle. Okay.

20:16.089 --> 20:18.217
What's up, Estelle?

20:18.258 --> 20:22.012
-How you doing?
       -Were you born in 1959?

20:22.054 --> 20:22.763
No.

20:22.804 --> 20:25.515
Then don't call me
          by my first name.

20:25.557 --> 20:27.643
My bad, Ms. Dubois.

20:27.684 --> 20:30.437
-You still ain't got no job?
             -Trust me.

20:30.479 --> 20:32.147
If I did,
      I wouldn't be up in here.

20:32.189 --> 20:34.399
-Don't get smart.
      -What you want me to do?

20:34.441 --> 20:36.193
I want you to get
           out of my face.

20:36.235 --> 20:38.153
Okay. Then give me a job.

20:38.195 --> 20:40.405
It ain't my fault
      that the economy is bad.

20:40.447 --> 20:43.158
-It ain't my fault either.
      -I manage to keep a job.

20:43.200 --> 20:45.077
Yeah, 'cause can't
      nobody else keep theirs.

20:45.118 --> 20:46.286
You see all those people
             out there?

20:46.328 --> 20:49.706
Well, thank you for making
      sure I have job security.

20:49.748 --> 20:51.792
Is that supposed
            to be a joke?

20:51.833 --> 20:53.752
Do you think
         this shit is funny?

20:53.794 --> 20:57.172
I'm broke, Ms. Dubois.
            I need help.

20:57.214 --> 20:58.423
Okay? Help me.

20:58.465 --> 21:01.343
You need to get that...
         crust out your eye.

21:01.385 --> 21:03.303
I don't know why
       you need so much sleep.

21:03.345 --> 21:06.431
Black folks need rest,
          too, Ms. Dubois,

21:06.473 --> 21:08.475
and jobs.

21:08.517 --> 21:10.435
I don't have anything
             right now,

21:10.477 --> 21:12.354
so you gonna have
      to come back next month.

21:12.396 --> 21:15.774
Ms. Dubois, I thought
      we was better than that.

21:15.816 --> 21:17.693
We're not.

21:17.734 --> 21:19.903
So you ain't gonna
         help me get a job?

21:21.697 --> 21:23.448
How the hell you get fired?

21:23.490 --> 21:24.950
Ma, I really don't wanna
            get into it.

21:24.992 --> 21:26.618
Mm-hmm, 'cause you
    was probably doing some shit

21:26.660 --> 21:28.287
you wasn't supposed
        to be doing, Hattie.

21:28.328 --> 21:30.747
Why you always assuming
       I did something wrong?

21:30.789 --> 21:33.208
Did you end up doing
      the nasty with your boss?

21:33.250 --> 21:34.501
Ma, oh, my God.

21:34.543 --> 21:36.461
I am not talking about that
              with you.

21:36.503 --> 21:37.546
See, that's your problem.

21:37.587 --> 21:39.506
You always running
          after these women

21:39.548 --> 21:41.633
you ain't got no business
           running after.

21:41.675 --> 21:44.261
Well, she did read
          my script though.

21:44.303 --> 21:46.096
Well, what she say?

21:46.138 --> 21:47.597
She said it was good,

21:47.639 --> 21:49.683
but that I need
       to keep working on it.

21:49.725 --> 21:53.312
Well, hell, she got
     about 18 shows on the air,

21:53.353 --> 21:55.856
so maybe you should work on it.

21:55.897 --> 21:57.774
Yeah, maybe.

22:01.236 --> 22:02.946
Hey, Ma, you still got
             that hookup

22:02.988 --> 22:04.156
at that delivery service?

22:04.197 --> 22:08.160
-Yeah.
              -I, um...

22:08.201 --> 22:10.329
I might need you
      to put in a call for me.

22:10.370 --> 22:12.372
Why? You need some money?

22:12.414 --> 22:15.083
Nah, I just...

22:15.125 --> 22:17.210
need a job.

22:18.587 --> 22:22.299
All right.
       I'll beep him tomorrow.

22:22.341 --> 22:24.968
Your friend
        still uses a beeper?

22:25.010 --> 22:26.470
Yeah.

22:26.511 --> 22:28.805
He old school like that,
        you know, pimp daddy.

22:28.847 --> 22:31.516
--He still burning CDs too.

22:31.558 --> 22:33.977
CDs?
      Damn, can he burn me one?

22:34.019 --> 22:34.936
Yeah. What you want?

22:34.978 --> 22:36.813
Tell him I want a Whitney
           and Prince mix.

22:36.855 --> 22:39.524
Tell him, don't forget to put
        "You Give Good Love" on.

22:39.566 --> 22:40.901
Oh, hold up, he--
            now, you know

22:40.942 --> 22:43.487
he gonna charge extra
          for two artists.

22:43.528 --> 22:44.905
You know
         I ain't got no money.

22:44.946 --> 22:46.198
Mm-hmm.

22:46.239 --> 22:47.741
-I got you, girl.
           -Thank you, Ma.

22:47.783 --> 22:49.284
Do you don't need
             anything else?

22:49.326 --> 22:50.494
You all right?

22:50.535 --> 22:53.163
I mean, you got $50?

22:53.205 --> 22:54.581
No. Okay, girl, this static.

22:54.623 --> 22:56.541
-What?
    -It's breaking up. All right.

22:56.583 --> 22:59.378
-Come on, Ma. Damn.
             -Oh, girl.
